Within the framework of this course students acquire basics of Latin. The course will introduce grammatical system and principles of syntax of the Latin language.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give the students basic knowledge of Latin, of its grammatical structure and constructions of sentence.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The course will give an overview of the basic Latin grammar. By the end of the course, students will be able to find the stems of nouns, verbs and adjectives, to determine declensions of nouns and conjugations on verbs and to form correct morphological forms. They are able to translate different participle forms, to identify the most common pronouns and translate simpler texts in Latin. Students will be familiar with constructions "accusativus cum infinitivo" , "nominativus cum infinitivo" and "ablativus absolutus" and with the basic principles of the syntactic structure of Latin sentences.
